# Command prefixes treated as read-only. Used by the sandbox-disabled carve-out.
# A line matches if the (de-wrapped) command equals the line exactly OR starts
# with the line plus a space. Don't shorten "git log" to "git" or "gh pr" to
# "gh" — that would also cover write-capable subcommands.

